<article id="post-634" class="post-634 page type-page status-publish hentry">
	<header class="entry-header">
		<h1 class="entry-title">Oxford University Strategic Studies Group (OUSSG)</h1>
	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

	<div class="entry-content">
		<div style="text-align: left;" align="left">Professor Sir Hew Strachan is currently Senior Member of the student-run Oxford University Strategic Studies Group (OUSSG). The group was founded with the assistance of military historian, Professor Sir Michael Howard OM CH KBE MC, over forty years ago as a non-partisan society devoted to the examination of contemporary strategic and international affairs through speaking events and field study trips. The central feature of its activities is a weekly seminar, which is given by distinguished men and women from the diplomatic, military, political, intelligence, academic, business and media fields.</div>
<div style="text-align: left;" align="left"></div>
<div style="text-align: left;" align="left">Annual membership of OUSSG is priced at £20. Non-members are welcome but will be charged a £2 entry fee at each event. An application form is available from <a href="mailto:treasurer@oussg.org">treasurer@oussg.org</a>. Upon completion of your application, a membership card will be delivered to you. Further information is available from the website (<span style="text-decoration: underline;"><a href="http://www.oussg.org">http://www.oussg.org</a></span>). OUSSG also has a <a href="http://oussg.us2.list-manage.com/track/click?u=b4e34df7b2bcaeed3c4a182aa&amp;id=e31c6cdaf0&amp;e=b43902d804" target="_blank">Facebook</a> group, and you can follow them on <a href="http://oussg.us2.list-manage.com/track/click?u=b4e34df7b2bcaeed3c4a182aa&amp;id=a2daed9703&amp;e=b43902d804" target="_blank">Twitter</a>.The OUSSG committee is: President, Josh Brown (Merton); Vice President, Joe Riley (St. John&#8217;s); Corporate Affairs Officer (and newly-wed), Jon Askonas (St. Cross); Treasurer, Karlson Leung (St. Cross); and Rupert Yorke (St Anne&#8217;s).</div>
<div style="text-align: left;" align="left"></div>
<div style="text-align: left;" align="left"><strong>HILARY 2015 TERM CARD</strong></div>
<div style="text-align: left;" align="left"></div>
<div style="text-align: left;" align="left">1st Week: <strong>Sir RICHARD OTTAWAY, Chair, Foreign Relations Select Committee, House of Commons</strong><br />
<em>A World in Turmoil</em><br />
Wednesday January 21 | 20:30 &#8211; 22:00</p>
<p>2nd Week: <strong>Acting Ambassador IHOR KYZYM, Embassy of Ukraine to the United Kingdom</strong><br />
<em>Supporting Ukraine: A Stronger and United Europe</em><br />
Tuesday January 27 | 20:30 &#8211; 22:00</p>
<p>3rd Week: <strong>Sir STEPHEN WALL, Former British Permanent Representative to the EU</strong><br />
<em>Britain and the EU: Why do we love to hate it?</em><br />
Tuesday February 3 | 20:30 &#8211; 22:00</p>
<p>4th Week: <strong>Professor WILLIAM CALLAHAN, Department of International Relations, </strong><strong>LSE</strong><br />
<em>China&#8217;s World Dream</em><br />
Wednesday February 11 | 20:30 &#8211; 22:00</p>
<p>5th Week: <strong>Ambassador DOUGLAS LUTE, United States Permanent Representative to NATO</strong><br />
<em>Wales to Warsaw: NATO and the Transatlantic Security Environment</em><br />
Tuesday February 17 | 20:30 &#8211; 22:00</p>
<p>6th Week:<strong><br />
Colonel CHRISTOPHER KOLENDA, Senior Military Fellow, KCL</strong><br />
<em>Succeeding From Failure: Problems to Avoid in Future Conflicts</em><br />
Tuesday February 24 | 20:30 &#8211; 22:00</p>
<p>7th Week: <strong>CHARLIE EDWARDS, Director, National Security and Resilience Studies, RUSI</strong><br />
<em>UK Counter-Terrorism Strategy and the 2015 Strategic Defence and Security Review</em><br />
Tuesday March 3 | 20:30 &#8211; 22:00</p>
<p>8th Week: <strong>JANE KINNINMONT, Deputy Head &amp; Senior Research Fellow, Middle East and North Africa Programme, Chatham House</strong><br />
<em>Shifting Geopolitics in the Middle East</em><br />
Tuesday March 10 | 20:30 &#8211; 22:00</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
